                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d304">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1121 Fernandez, Antonio/178: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-05T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 5, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>B–449. Your despatch no. 1433 of February 9, 1938,<note n="86" xml:id="d304fn86"
                        >Not printed, but see the Ambassador’s telegram No. 445, February 8, 7 p.m.,
                            <ref target="#pg_271">p. 271</ref>.</note> Antonio Fernandez and wife.
                    Information received by Vice Consul Fisher from Palma de Mallorca and in letters
                    from Antonio Fernandez to his brother in New York indicate that he has been
                    hospitalized suffering from chronic nervous ailment aggravated by continued
                    imprisonment. In view of assurances of favorable consideration of case given in
                    General Jordana’s letter of February 5, 1938 and the long time which has since
                    elapsed, you are requested again to bring this case informally to the attention
                    of General Jordana and to express the hope that in view of Fernandez’ physical
                    condition it may be possible to permit his release and return to the United
                    States together with his wife.<note n="87" xml:id="d304fn87">By telegram No.
                        509, August 6, 1 p.m., the Ambassador reported that a letter had gone that
                        day to General Jordana (352.1121 Fernandez, Antonio/177).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
